class_description: The abstract class NSEnumerator provides a convenience implementation that uses nextObject() to return items one at a time.

Methods.method_description: Returns by reference a C array of objects over which the sender should iterate, and as the return value the number of objects in the array.Required.

params.param_description: Context information that is used in the enumeration to, in addition to other possibilities, ensure that the collection has not been mutated.
The maximum number of objects to return in stackbuf.

Methods.method_declar: func countByEnumerating(with state: UnsafeMutablePointer<NSFastEnumerationState>, objects buffer: AutoreleasingUnsafeMutablePointer<AnyObject?>, count len: Int) -> Int

return_description: The number of objects returned in stackbuf. Returns 0 when the iteration is finished.
